<dl id="s18016bn"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us18" href="#s18016bn">Penelope: </a><a href="../../FF/unbs/s18all.htm#s18016bn">sector 16(bn)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> political refugees</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Besides the garrison, and the English or Spanish residents of Gibraltar, the town has a floating population as motley in race and color as can be found in any city on the Mediterranean. Indeed it is one of the most cosmopolitan places in the world. It is a great resort of <mark>political refugees</mark>, who seek protection under the English flag. As it is so close to Spain, it is the first refuge of Spanish conspirators, who, failing in their attempts at revolution, flee across the lines. <small> Henry M. Field, <a name="HMFG" href="/udra/udex.htm#HMFG"><cite title="source">Gibralter</cite></a> (1888), p 33</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
